title: TRAVEL: East Coast main line disrupted after overnight incident
text:
Credit: David Parry/PA Archive/PA Images Virgin Trains East Coast services have been disrupted overnight due to emergency services dealing with an incident at Darlington.
The firm had said their services were no longer affected by the incident but the 05.59am service from Newcastle to London King's Cross has been cancelled.
Virgin Trains EC @Virgin_TrainsEC Follow #VTECDelay The 05:59 Newcastle to London King's Cross will be cancelled due to emergency services dealing with a prior incident.
